 <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token plain-text\"> alert—check it out!\n            </span><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span><span class=\"token class-name\">Alert</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n          <span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n        <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n      <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token plain-text\">\n    </span><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n</code></pre>\n</figure>\n<div class=\"bd-callout bd-callout-warning\"><h5 id=\"conveying-meaning-to-assistive-technologies\">Conveying meaning to assistive technologies</h5>\n<p>Using color to add meaning only provides a visual indication, which will not be conveyed to users of assistive technologies – such as screen readers. Ensure that information denoted by the color is either obvious from the content itself (e.g. the visible text), or is included through alternative means, such as additional text hidden with the <code>.sr-only</code> class.</p>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"link-color\">Link color</h3>\n<p>Use the <code>Alert.Link</code> component to quickly provide matching colored links within any alert.</p>\n<div class=\"bd-example\" id=\"mvvm_typede90426acb8f600ed982b553147d1658\" data-mvvm-type=\"mexample_with_code\" data-sample-defaultopen=\"\">\n</div>\n\n<script type=\"text/plain\" data-js-id=mvvm_typede90426acb8f600ed982b553147d1658>var Sample = function Sample() {\n  return React.createElement(React.Fragment, null, site.data['theme-colors'].map(function (color) {\n    return React.createElement(Alert, {\n      theme: color.name\n    }, \"A simple \", color.name, \" alert with\", ' ', React.createElement(Alert.Link, {\n      href: \"#\"\n    }, \"an example link\"), \". Give it a click if you like.\");\n  }));\n};\n\nReactDOM.render(React.createElement(Sample, {\n  uuid: 'de90426acb8f600ed982b553147d1658'\n}), document.getElementById('mvvm_typede90426acb8f600ed982b553147d1658'));</script>\n\n<div class=\"bd-clipboard\">\n                    <button type=\"button\" class=\"btn-sample-collapse\" title=\"\" data-original-title=\"Toggle the sample\">\n                        Toggle Code\n                    </button>\n                    <button type=\"button\" class=\"btn-clipboard\" title=\"\" data-original-title=\"Copy to clipboard\">\n                        Copy\n                    </button>\n                </div><figure class=\"highlight\"><pre><code class=\"language-jsx\">\n<span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> <span class=\"token function-variable function\">Sample</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=></span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">return</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>\n    <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span><span class=\"token plain-text\">\n      </span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>site<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>data<span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token string\">'theme-colors'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span>\n        <span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">map</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token parameter\">color</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=></span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n          <span class=\"token keyword\">return</span> <span class=\"to