>\n</code></pre>\n</figure>\n<h3 id=\"dismissing\">Dismissing</h3>\n<p>Using the alert JavaScript plugin, it&#39;s possible to dismiss any alert inline. Here&#39;s how:</p>\n<p>You can see this in action with a live demo:</p>\n<div class=\"bd-example\" id=\"mvvm_type86a9400e45844c078e8e223ceef6dd60\" data-mvvm-type=\"mexample_with_code\" data-sample-defaultopen=\"\">\n</div>\n\n<script type=\"text/plain\" data-js-id=mvvm_type86a9400e45844c078e8e223ceef6dd60>var Sample = function Sample() {\n  return React.createElement(React.Fragment, null, React.createElement(Alert, {\n    theme: \"warning\",\n    closable: true\n  }, React.createElement(\"strong\", null, \"Holy guacamole!\"), \" You should check in on some of those fields below.\"));\n};\n\nReactDOM.render(React.createElement(Sample, {\n  uuid: '86a9400e45844c078e8e223ceef6dd60'\n}), document.getElementById('mvvm_type86a9400e45844c078e8e223ceef6dd60'));</script>\n\n<div class=\"bd-clipboard\">\n                    <button type=\"button\" class=\"btn-sample-collapse\" title=\"\" data-original-title=\"Toggle the sample\">\n                        Toggle Code\n                    </button>\n                    <button type=\"button\" class=\"btn-clipboard\" title=\"\" data-original-title=\"Copy to clipboard\">\n                        Copy\n                    </button>\n                </div><figure class=\"highlight\"><pre><code class=\"language-jsx\">\n<span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> <span class=\"token function-variable function\">Sample</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=></span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">return</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>\n    <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span><span cla